ion API extracts text structured as JSON; drag-and-drop handles state. |\n| Risk | 8/10 | No complex banking APIs; simple deep-linking handles transactions safely. |\n| Impact | 9/10 | Clear physical-to-digital utility shown instantly in a 10-second demo. |\n| **TOTAL** | **42/50** | |\n| **4. Explain Back (Education)** | | |\n| Market Need | 8/10 | Active recall and the Feynman technique are highly prized but hard to self-evaluate. |\n| Differentiation | 9/10 | Flips the paradigm: AI audits *your* understanding rather than lecturing you. |\n| Feasibility | 8/10 | Uses text-diffing LLM calls comparing a user prompt to a reference syllabus/text. |\n| Risk | 8/10 | Mild risk of subjective grading, but highly mitigated by clear UI annotations. |\n| Impact | 8/10 | Genuinely educational, shifting the needle on AI study tools. |\n| **TOTAL** | **41/50** | |\n| **5. Mockup (Developer Tools)** | | |\n| Market Need | 8/10 | Setting up database schemas and initial mock API endpoints is tedious. |\n| Differentiation | 8/10 | Combines interactive visual ERD generation with dynamic, ephemeral mock endpoints. |\n| Feasibility | 8/10 | Highly feasible; uses Mermaid.js for visual rendering and serverless edge functions. |\n| Risk | 8/10 | Relies on LLM JSON generation consistency, but highly controllable. |\n| Impact | 8/10 | Saves developer hours instantly; great technical depth presentation. |\n| **TOTAL** | **40/50** | |\n\n---\n\n### Top 3 Recommendations\n\n1. **Tailwinds (Screenshot to Live UI)**: A masterclass in utility and presentation. It provides an immediate, functional tool that solves a massive dev paint point without any complex integration overhead.\n2. **StoryCraft (Bedtime Choose-Your-Own-Adventure)**: Taps into emotional appeal, high-fidelity UI design (book-flipping animation), and fast vector generation, ensuring the 30-second demo is unforgettable. \n3. **SplitSecond (Visual Receipt Allocator)**: An incredibly relatable consumer utility. It bypasses complex b